<head>
<title>DIE-IF-NO-SUGAR</title>

</head>
<body>
	<h3><i>I die if I have no more sugar.</i> </h3>

	<p><font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font> </p>
	<p><b>DIE-IF-NO-SUGAR </b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>do-after .003
   [do-every 1
       [do-if my-sugar &lt;= 0
           [add-behaviours list-of-micro-behaviours &quot;Behaviours when no sugar" [DIE.html]]]]</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p>This ensures that

	<a title="DIE" href="DIE.html">DIE</a> runs 

	if my sugar becomes zero or less. Sugar consumption is implemented by

	<a title="CONSUME-SUGAR-DELAYED" href="CONSUME-SUGAR-DELAYED.html">

	CONSUME-SUGAR-DELAYED</a>.

	<a title="DIE-IF-TOO-OLD" href="DIE-IF-TOO-OLD.html">

	DIE-IF-TOO-OLD</a> is another way to die. </p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>This delays the test of whether <i>my-sugar</i> has gotten too low by 

	.003 time units to be sure this runs after

	<a title="CONSUME-SUGAR" href="CONSUME-SUGAR.html">

	CONSUME-SUGAR</a>. </p>

	<h2>Source</h2>
	<p>Based upon page 25 of [1]. </p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn. </p>

	<h2>References</h2>

	<p>[1] <i>Growing Artificial Societies</i> by Joshua M. Epstein and Robert 

	Axtell, Brookings Institute Press, The MIT Press, 1996. 
